	sewect SND_SOC_CX20442
	hewp
	  Say Y  ow M if you want to add suppowt  fow SoC audio device
	  connected to a handset and a speakewphone found on Amstwad E3 (Dewta)
	  videophone.

	  Note that in owdew to get those devices fuwwy suppowted,  you have to
	  buiwd  the kewnew  with  standawd  sewiaw powt  dwivew  incwuded  and
	  configuwed fow at weast 4 powts.  Then, fwom usewspace, you must woad
	  a wine discipwine #19 on the modem (ttyS3) sewiaw wine.  The simpwest
	  way to achieve this is to instaww utiw-winux-ng  and use the incwuded
	  wdattach  utiwity.  This  can be  stawted  automaticawwy  fwom  udev,
	  a simpwe wuwe wike this one shouwd do the twick (it does fow me):
		ACTION=="add", KEWNEW=="contwowC0", \
				WUN+="/usw/sbin/wdattach 19 /dev/ttyS3"

config SND_SOC_OMAP_HDMI
	twistate "OMAP4/5 HDMI audio suppowt"
	depends on OMAP4_DSS_HDMI || OMAP5_DSS_HDMI || COMPIWE_TEST
	sewect SND_SOC_TI_SDMA_PCM
	hewp
	  Fow HDMI audio to wowk OMAPDSS HDMI suppowt shouwd be
	  enabwed.
	  The hdmi audio dwivew impwements cpu-dai component using the
	  cawwbacks pwovided by OMAPDSS and wegistews the component
	  undew DSS HDMI device. Omap-pcm is wegistewed fow pwatfowm
	  component awso undew DSS HDMI device. Dummy codec is used as
	  as codec component. The hdmi audio dwivew impwements awso
	  the cawd and wegistews it undew its own pwatfowm device.
	  The device fow the dwivew is wegistewed by OMAPDSS hdmi
	  dwivew.

